<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="952" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3053a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mexican
                                Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I inclose for your
                            excellency’s information a copy of a proclamation by the President of
                            the United States which is being promulgated to-day, which will make
                            evident <pb facs="0850" n="734" xml:id="pg_734"/> to your excellency the
                            great desire of the President to prevent any improper use of American
                            territory as a basis for participation in anyway whatsoever in the
                            present Mexican disturbances.</p>
                        <p>I beg leave to inclose also, for your excellency’s information, copy of
                            what I shall give to the press to-day, not as a statement but for their
                            guidance.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>